analysisPopulations.name: Screened Set
analysisPopulations.label: Screened Set
analysisPopulations.description: The Screened Set will include all participants who signed an informed consent form (ICF).

analysisPopulations.name: Enrolled Set
analysisPopulations.label: Enrolled Set
analysisPopulations.description: The Enrolled Set will include all participants who signed an ICF and were enrolled in the study.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Signed an ICF and were enrolled in the study

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: FA Set
analysisPopulations.description: The Full Analysis (FA) Set will include all participants who were enrolled and received at least 1 dose of study drug. The FA Set will be the primary population for all efficacy analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Enrolled and received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Per Protocol Set
analysisPopulations.label: PP Set
analysisPopulations.description: The Per Protocol (PP) Set will include all participants in the FA Set who have no major protocol deviations that would impact the primary efficacy endpoint. The PP Set will be used for sensitivity analyses of the primary efficacy endpoint.
analysisPopulations.criteria: In the FA Set with no major protocol deviations impacting the primary efficacy endpoint

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Set
analysisPopulations.label: Safety Set
analysisPopulations.description: The Safety Set will include all participants who received at least 1 dose of study drug. The Safety Set will be used for all safety analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: PK Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.description: The Pharmacokinetic (PK) Analysis Set will include all participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient plasma concentration data to allow for the derivation of at least 1 PK parameter. The PK Analysis Set will be used for all PK analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: In the Safety Set with sufficient plasma concentration data to derive at least 1 PK parameter

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacodynamic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: PD Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.description: The Pharmacodynamic (PD) Analysis Set will include all participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient PD data to allow for the derivation of at least 1 PD parameter. The PD Analysis Set will be used for all PD analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: In the Safety Set with sufficient PD data to derive at least 1 PD parameter

characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Age calculated as the integer part of the number of years from the date of birth to the date of informed consent.

characteristics.name: Time since initial diagnosis of WD
characteristics.description: Time since initial diagnosis of Wilson Disease.

characteristics.name: Baseline clinical presentation
characteristics.description: Baseline clinical presentation (eg, hepatic, neurologic, psychiatric, or asymptomatic).

characteristics.name: Medical/Surgical History
characteristics.description: Medical and surgical history coded using MedDRA.

characteristics.name: Wilson Disease history
characteristics.description: History of Wilson Disease, summarized separately.

characteristics.name: Prior medications for WD
characteristics.description: Prior medications used to treat Wilson Disease, summarized separately.

characteristics.name: Baseline copper balance
characteristics.description: Pretreatment assessment of copper balance measured from Day -4 through Day -1.

characteristics.name: Baseline molybdenum balance
characteristics.description: Pretreatment assessment of molybdenum balance measured from Day -4 through Day -1.
